main event: Observation of two white objects moving slower than a meteor but faster than a plane in Toledo, Ohio on February 6, 1968.
interesting points: The witness did not return the AF Form 117 within 30 days., The objects were reported to be moving faster than a plane., Data is incomplete due to lack of further documentation., The report was generated by the Air Force's Project Blue Book., The observation took place around 6:45 to 7:00 PM under clear conditions.
witness description: one witness who did not submit the required form
